WEBVTT

00:05.625 --> 00:06.667
Previously
on  Billions...

00:06.750 --> 00:10.083
They're in this. I can't
look away from it anymore.

00:10.166 --> 00:12.959
The Ice Juice short,
how do I get a piece of that?

00:13.041 --> 00:14.959
-I can make it happen.
-As much as I can get.

00:15.041 --> 00:17.166
Will your father hold up
under questioning?

00:17.250 --> 00:19.250
He's not taking my counsel
at the moment.

00:19.333 --> 00:19.750
Do you want access?

00:19.834 --> 00:22.583
Yes, I believe I do.

00:24.458 --> 00:26.750
Just trace amounts
on my signal.

00:26.834 --> 00:29.583
We have you
pissing in the soup.

00:29.667 --> 00:31.709
And people's lives
were placed in jeopardy.

00:31.792 --> 00:33.583
I was told
they weren't in any danger--

00:33.667 --> 00:35.667
The man who instructed you.
Describe him.

00:35.750 --> 00:39.166
Fifties. Bald.
Glasses...

00:39.250 --> 00:41.583
After 18 hours,
the toxin would evaporate.

00:41.667 --> 00:43.792
Do you want us
to check his lab?

00:43.875 --> 00:44.875
And his home.

00:44.959 --> 00:47.166
I told you:
I disposed of the slide.

00:47.250 --> 00:48.166
How?

00:48.250 --> 00:49.750
You have to trust me.

00:49.834 --> 00:51.542
If you don't want
to get on the stand,

00:51.625 --> 00:53.917
then there needs to be
physical evidence.

00:54.000 --> 00:56.041
An item that
could speak for you.

00:56.125 --> 00:57.625
Finally got my read.

00:57.709 --> 01:00.959
He's made a deal with
the government, and I'm fucked.

01:07.208 --> 01:10.542
♪ dramatic music  ♪

01:10.625 --> 01:14.041
♪♪♪

01:14.125 --> 01:17.500
♪♪♪

01:21.792 --> 01:26.667
♪♪♪

01:26.750 --> 01:30.834
♪♪♪

01:30.917 --> 01:34.875
♪ Keep me  ♪

01:34.959 --> 01:37.834
♪ Sinking down  ♪

01:37.917 --> 01:40.000
We wear them
for two reasons.

01:40.083 --> 01:42.166
To keep the aromas
from escaping,

01:42.250 --> 01:47.458
and to hide this shameful
and depraved act

01:47.542 --> 01:49.458
from god.

01:49.542 --> 01:51.834
Well, if there were
a god, I think he'd know.

01:51.917 --> 01:55.125
♪ Keep my feet  ♪

01:55.208 --> 01:57.667
♪ On the ground  ♪

01:57.750 --> 02:02.041
♪♪♪

02:05.583 --> 02:06.542
Fifty thousand.

02:06.625 --> 02:09.041
The other 50 and the visas
for your family

02:09.125 --> 02:10.375
you will get
on completion.

02:10.458 --> 02:11.917
-Thank you.
-If all goes well,

02:12.000 --> 02:14.542
we'll have them out of Congo
and in the States by summer.

02:14.625 --> 02:16.375
And your Axelrod will be
where I once was.

02:16.458 --> 02:16.875
Mm.

02:16.959 --> 02:18.917
You have the item?

02:22.375 --> 02:23.500
In here.

02:25.000 --> 02:28.917
Now, the slide has an 18 hour
half-life at room temperature,

02:29.000 --> 02:31.166
so make sure you plant it
in Axe's medicine cabinet

02:31.250 --> 02:32.875
or someplace
away from sunlight.

02:32.959 --> 02:35.208
Infiltration of
Axelrod's penthouse

02:35.291 --> 02:37.333
involves the highest degree
of difficulty.

02:37.417 --> 02:41.291
However, he will be
at Art Basel in three weeks--

02:41.375 --> 02:43.000
--The luxe life
rolls on unabated--

02:43.083 --> 02:45.792
--Mechanical work is scheduled
while he's away.

02:45.875 --> 02:49.166
I will, uh, execute then.

02:49.250 --> 02:53.792
♪ suspenseful music  ♪

02:53.875 --> 02:57.875
♪ dramatic music  ♪

03:01.959 --> 03:03.166
Look, I don't want you
to get in trouble.

03:03.250 --> 03:03.917
I won't.

03:04.000 --> 03:05.458
Do you even know who I--

03:05.542 --> 03:06.291
Why don't you get on
the little earpiece

03:06.375 --> 03:09.250
and talk to the people
in there?

03:09.333 --> 03:10.750
I am Head of Compliance.

03:10.834 --> 03:12.250
Authorized personnel only.

03:12.333 --> 03:13.917
They'll authorize me.

03:14.000 --> 03:16.291
You're not on the list.

03:16.375 --> 03:17.917
But those two are?

03:18.000 --> 03:21.250
Jury consultants.

03:21.333 --> 03:24.375
You give a guy
a little bit of authority.

03:24.458 --> 03:25.834
Mason, Taylor.

03:25.917 --> 03:26.333
Nope.

03:30.542 --> 03:34.166
They're clearly jealous
of my standing in the company.

03:34.250 --> 03:35.709
Pricks.

03:37.041 --> 03:41.709
♪ suspenseful music  ♪

03:41.792 --> 03:43.375
Status on the slide?

03:43.458 --> 03:45.834
The slide is not
in evidence at Eastern.

03:45.917 --> 03:47.792
Officially.

03:47.875 --> 03:49.500
Somehow that doesn't
give me comfort.

03:49.583 --> 03:51.166
Even if we could compromise
an assistant at Eastern

03:51.250 --> 03:53.041
or remotely access
the FBI case file--

03:53.125 --> 03:55.458
They'd hide it
under a code name.

03:55.542 --> 03:59.375
Our motion to dismiss
is a much more direct solution.

03:59.458 --> 04:02.166
If Eastern has the slide,
the motion forces them

04:02.250 --> 04:04.583
to reveal the evidence
to prove they have a case.

04:04.667 --> 04:05.792
And if they don't?

04:05.875 --> 04:07.583
Bryan Connerty
has very little

04:07.667 --> 04:10.166
on which to mount
his prosecution.

04:14.917 --> 04:17.333
If you come in, you got to
retain Bach's services.

04:17.417 --> 04:18.750
Attorney-client privilege.

04:23.583 --> 04:25.375
I don't need ya
that  bad.

04:25.458 --> 04:27.500
♪ suspenseful music  ♪

04:27.583 --> 04:30.834
♪♪♪

04:30.917 --> 04:33.291
Ooh.

04:33.917 --> 04:36.500
Thank you.

04:36.583 --> 04:38.625
Nice weeds.

04:38.709 --> 04:41.041
So, this guy or...

04:41.125 --> 04:42.083
girl or...whatever

04:42.166 --> 04:44.458
couldn't spring for roses?

04:44.542 --> 04:46.500
I'd have gotten you
a k.d. lang album

04:46.583 --> 04:48.917
and tickets to UFC,
cover all the bases.

04:49.000 --> 04:50.875
They're delphiniums.

04:53.125 --> 04:53.917
The petals are clustered

04:54.000 --> 04:56.375
according to
the Fibonacci Sequence.

04:56.458 --> 04:58.250
Also called
the Golden Ratio.

04:59.792 --> 05:01.375
It's a series of numbers
in which each number is

05:01.458 --> 05:04.125
the sum of the two
preceding numbers.

05:04.208 --> 05:06.875
It's frequently echoed
in art and in nature.

05:06.959 --> 05:09.333
That's a good gift
too, then.

05:09.417 --> 05:13.333
So, who's
the lucky...person?

05:13.417 --> 05:15.208
Hmm.

05:17.000 --> 05:17.500
From "Oscar."

05:19.291 --> 05:23.709
Recent trip
to Silicon Valley.

05:23.792 --> 05:24.458
Langstraat?

05:26.417 --> 05:27.959
A big billie.

05:28.041 --> 05:29.208
Nice.

05:29.291 --> 05:31.375
That long distance shit
works for you?

05:31.458 --> 05:33.834
If we were in the same place,
but each drawn to work

05:33.917 --> 05:35.917
with 90 percent of our time,
it would be awkward,

05:36.000 --> 05:38.291
or make it seem like
our feelings didn't matter.

05:38.375 --> 05:39.500
This is better.

05:39.583 --> 05:41.750
♪ slow music  ♪

05:41.834 --> 05:45.750
♪♪♪

05:45.834 --> 05:48.917
♪♪♪

05:49.000 --> 05:52.875
♪♪♪

05:52.959 --> 05:54.542
Yo, quants.

05:56.375 --> 05:59.125
You have back-test results
for me?

05:59.208 --> 06:01.542
This is based on the exact
specs you gave me.

06:03.750 --> 06:07.458
Not exactly, no. The specs
I gave you were not a wish list.

06:07.542 --> 06:09.333
They included a threshold
for returns,

06:09.417 --> 06:11.333
which this simulation
fails to meet.

06:11.417 --> 06:13.625
Can you give us
next steps, then?

06:13.709 --> 06:14.750
Vary position size
when the system

06:14.834 --> 06:18.000
underperforms the market,
re-test and report back.

06:27.583 --> 06:29.542
You know, every time
I eat pig's ears,

06:29.625 --> 06:32.083
I'm reminded of how alert
and alive they once were.

06:32.166 --> 06:35.041
Makes me feel
a little bad.

06:35.125 --> 06:36.625
Favorite thing
on the menu.

06:36.709 --> 06:38.917
Of course, you can have them
slice it for you

06:39.000 --> 06:40.375
if it offends
your sensibilities.

06:40.458 --> 06:42.917
No. I feel a little bad
about a lot of things I do.

06:45.000 --> 06:46.458
Doesn't stop me.

06:46.542 --> 06:47.792
That's the way.

06:47.875 --> 06:49.917
Mmm!

06:50.000 --> 06:51.709
Zinfandel goes
nicely, too.

06:51.792 --> 06:53.250
Mm.

06:57.583 --> 07:00.166
We need to begin
time-lining your run.

07:00.250 --> 07:02.500
Scheduling events.
Introducing you to some people.

07:02.583 --> 07:04.917
Uh, we couldn't, not while
I'm still in office.

07:05.000 --> 07:08.000
Not as an official candidate,
of course.

07:08.083 --> 07:09.959
But we'll have
some dinners.

07:10.041 --> 07:11.000
Casual.

07:11.083 --> 07:13.333
But not at all casual.

07:13.417 --> 07:15.417
For the money folk,
it's a lot like watching

07:15.500 --> 07:18.667
morning workouts
at Churchill Downs.

07:18.750 --> 07:19.458
They get a feel for you.

07:19.542 --> 07:22.834
They, uh,
assess your stride.

07:22.917 --> 07:24.917
Then they decide how much
they're gonna wager.

07:25.000 --> 07:27.375
Mm. While I work up
a good sweat.

07:27.458 --> 07:28.875
I look forward to it.

07:31.500 --> 07:34.542
I need to know
you're squared away.

07:34.625 --> 07:37.959
I'm as locked down as a Firstie
at West Point, sir.

07:38.041 --> 07:42.041
The Axelrod situation will
resolve itself very soon,

07:42.125 --> 07:43.208
and favorably.

07:43.291 --> 07:44.959
Then I will
be unencumbered.

07:46.834 --> 07:49.041
How's your marriage?

07:49.125 --> 07:51.500
Well, a man who makes
proclamations on that

07:51.583 --> 07:52.959
tempts fate.

07:53.041 --> 07:56.208
But solid.

07:56.291 --> 07:57.625
Good.

07:57.709 --> 07:59.291
Well, if you do have
a good one,

07:59.375 --> 08:00.083
the campaign'll push it
to the brink.

08:00.166 --> 08:02.542
-Mm.
-If you don't--

08:02.625 --> 08:04.875
if there are
any weaknesses--

08:04.959 --> 08:06.166
it'll blow out
like a bad sidewall.

08:06.250 --> 08:08.250
No concern there.

08:08.333 --> 08:11.709
I'll need to sit with her.

08:15.417 --> 08:17.375
Grand. Do it.

08:17.458 --> 08:19.709
Good.
Well, very good, really.

08:21.709 --> 08:22.542
Nice eye contact.

08:22.625 --> 08:25.834
You've always been
a man of purpose.

08:25.917 --> 08:27.667
Which is exactly
what we need.

08:27.750 --> 08:31.625
But we'll also turn you
into a man of the people.

08:33.625 --> 08:36.250
I look forward
to meeting Wendy.

08:39.667 --> 08:41.500
♪ dramatic music  ♪

08:41.583 --> 08:44.083
♪♪♪

08:44.166 --> 08:47.583
♪♪♪

08:47.667 --> 08:50.792
This is it, right,

08:50.875 --> 08:52.625
the dismissal hearing?

08:52.709 --> 08:54.250
Boss, I got
a good feeling about this.

08:54.333 --> 08:55.500
Glad you're
so confident.

08:55.583 --> 08:57.333
Already put
the Pink Champipple on ice.

08:57.417 --> 08:58.917
Any day now,
you're gonna be back to trading,

08:59.000 --> 09:01.041
and everything'll
be like it's supposed to.

09:01.125 --> 09:03.000
Hold the bubbly,
Billy Buck Buck.

09:03.083 --> 09:05.375
-No premature cele--
-Today's about recon.

09:05.458 --> 09:06.709
I'll look
in their faces;

09:06.792 --> 09:08.625
see if they have
something to hide.

09:08.709 --> 09:10.125
Great suit.

09:10.208 --> 09:12.458
Bespoke? Are those
surgeon's cuffs?

09:12.542 --> 09:13.625
Not a good time, leech.

09:13.709 --> 09:15.083
Am I gonna have to
Mills Lane

09:15.166 --> 09:16.417
every interaction
between you two?

09:16.500 --> 09:17.750
-'Course not, come on.
-You're on your way to court.

09:17.834 --> 09:21.458
Remember this: I've worked
with Bryan Connerty,

09:21.542 --> 09:22.667
studied him.

09:22.750 --> 09:23.709
I can mirror the way
the guy thinks.

09:23.792 --> 09:25.500
You ever want to bounce
anything off of me...

09:25.583 --> 09:28.542
We know where
to find ya. Thanks.

09:28.625 --> 09:30.583
Anyway, I'm right.

09:30.667 --> 09:32.250
I feel it in my 'nads.

09:32.333 --> 09:34.834
Are they ever wrong?

09:34.917 --> 09:36.125
Spring break
senior year.

09:36.208 --> 09:38.458
Señor Frog's.

09:38.542 --> 09:40.959
Other than that--
hundred percent.

09:43.917 --> 09:45.709
Go get 'em, Axe!

09:45.792 --> 09:47.166
♪ dramatic music  ♪

09:47.250 --> 09:51.208
♪♪♪

09:51.291 --> 09:54.917
♪♪♪

09:59.375 --> 10:00.500
Ready?

10:00.583 --> 10:01.542
I guess.

10:01.625 --> 10:03.667
I have the case, I just
don't have the evidence.

10:03.750 --> 10:04.917
Wrong answer.

10:05.000 --> 10:06.625
You know the mantra
over at the DEA?

10:06.709 --> 10:08.709
If you ain't got video,
you ain't got shit.

10:08.792 --> 10:11.166
Well, we ain't got video,
Oliver. We got theories.

10:11.250 --> 10:13.291
If I were DeGiulio
I'd dismiss this case.

10:13.375 --> 10:14.667
Well, I do that too;

10:14.750 --> 10:16.500
try and make each person's
argument in the courtroom

10:16.583 --> 10:18.291
ahead of time so I can
make the counter argument.

10:18.375 --> 10:19.625
But we don't have to
this time--

10:19.709 --> 10:22.583
they need to deal with
the high bar to dismiss,

10:22.667 --> 10:24.667
the customary deference
to Prosecution.

10:24.750 --> 10:25.834
Not to mention
that dismissal

10:25.917 --> 10:28.166
would be poor optics
for DeGiulio.

10:28.250 --> 10:30.208
-He wants  to sit this case.
-Mm.

10:30.291 --> 10:31.250
You know
Axelrod is guilty.

10:31.333 --> 10:34.041
Carry yourself with confidence
in the courtroom,

10:34.125 --> 10:35.500
and DeGiulio
will know it, too.

10:35.583 --> 10:36.458
Confidence?

10:36.542 --> 10:37.709
Not even Evel Knievel
could jump the gap

10:37.792 --> 10:40.333
between what I know
and what I can prove.

10:40.417 --> 10:42.792
Then I suggest you do
what Mr. Knievel always did.

10:42.875 --> 10:44.875
Rev her high.
Pray for mercy.

10:44.959 --> 10:46.583
Try to put her down
on the ramp.

10:46.667 --> 10:47.875
And hope you are
one of the elect.

10:52.000 --> 10:54.166
Mr. Bach,
it's your motion.

10:54.250 --> 10:56.291
-Move me.
-I will.

10:56.375 --> 10:59.291
Like Brian's Song.

10:59.375 --> 11:01.709
Because like Mr. Piccolo's
sad, short life,

11:01.792 --> 11:05.375
Prosecution's case
starts off hopeful

11:05.458 --> 11:07.625
but ends
in an untimely demise.

11:07.709 --> 11:09.792
Your Honor,
to date, the government

11:09.875 --> 11:10.750
hasn't alleged
sufficient evidence

11:10.834 --> 11:13.959
that Mr. Axelrod
is guilty of any charges.

11:14.041 --> 11:16.542
Yet my client
has been unfairly stripped

11:16.625 --> 11:18.083
of his ability
to trade--

11:18.166 --> 11:20.375
while his firm,
his employees,

11:20.458 --> 11:23.208
and his family
have all been destabilized.

11:23.291 --> 11:26.166
We ask that you bring
this baseless campaign

11:26.250 --> 11:27.500
to its conclusion.

11:27.583 --> 11:28.959
Your Honor, this
entire motion is premature.

11:29.041 --> 11:31.625
The jury gets to decide issues
on material fact.

11:31.709 --> 11:34.250
Whether or not
they believe the evidence.

11:34.333 --> 11:36.125
Mr. Bach is saying
there's no evidence

11:36.208 --> 11:36.959
for them to decide about.

11:37.041 --> 11:40.208
We are pursuing
several threads.

11:40.291 --> 11:41.959
So maybe it's not
this motion that's premature.

11:42.041 --> 11:44.083
Maybe it's
your whole prosecution.

11:44.166 --> 11:45.667
Testimony that
we initially promised to have,

11:45.750 --> 11:48.542
that we meant to have,
should have

11:48.625 --> 11:51.208
is not...available.

11:51.291 --> 11:53.583
We have reason to believe
that several of our witnesses

11:53.667 --> 11:54.792
have been tampered with.

11:54.875 --> 11:56.083
Your Honor--

11:56.166 --> 11:59.208
Mr. Bach, there's no jury to
hear your pained objections.

11:59.291 --> 12:01.709
Mr. Connerty,
do you have any evidence

12:01.792 --> 12:05.417
to back up that claim...for why
you don't have any evidence?

12:06.583 --> 12:08.000
Not at this time.

12:08.083 --> 12:11.208
Then...what do  you have
at this  time?

12:11.291 --> 12:13.291
We are pursuing information
about an operative

12:13.375 --> 12:14.792
we believe
is a direct link

12:14.875 --> 12:17.083
between Mr. Axelrod
and the contaminant

12:17.166 --> 12:19.291
that sabotaged
the juice company.

12:19.375 --> 12:21.250
You have him in custody?

12:21.333 --> 12:23.291
We are pursuing
the thread to him.

12:23.375 --> 12:25.041
So, in other words,
all you have is evidence

12:25.125 --> 12:26.500
against someone
who isn't me.

12:26.583 --> 12:29.333
Mr. Axelrod, do I look
like I need your help?

12:29.417 --> 12:32.667
Mr. Connerty, what do you know
about the operative so far?

12:32.750 --> 12:34.250
Does he
have a name?

12:34.333 --> 12:36.667
That's...part of what
we're trying to ascertain.

12:36.750 --> 12:39.208
We do have witnesses
that can ID him.

12:41.250 --> 12:42.917
If you find him.

12:43.166 --> 12:45.417
Yes.

12:45.500 --> 12:48.041
You a music fan,
Mr. Connerty?

12:49.709 --> 12:51.083
Sure. Much as
the next guy.

12:51.166 --> 12:53.125
Yo-Yo Ma,
Clancy Brothers and such.

12:53.208 --> 12:54.750
I'm thinking of
the great George Clinton.

12:54.834 --> 12:55.875
Who most famously said,

12:55.959 --> 12:57.750
"Free your mind
and your ass will follow."

12:57.834 --> 12:59.041
But only slightly
less known and far more apt

12:59.125 --> 13:02.709
in the case at bar is,
"You can't fake the funk."

13:02.792 --> 13:04.709
As much as I want
to dance to your tune,

13:04.792 --> 13:06.709
if the groove isn't fat enough,
I'm just gonna stand in place.

13:06.792 --> 13:09.166
And right now,
my feet aren't tapping.

13:09.250 --> 13:10.875
That said,
I don't think you're lying.

13:12.750 --> 13:13.834
I'm splitting the baby.

13:13.917 --> 13:15.166
I'm granting Mr. Connerty
one more week.

13:15.250 --> 13:17.792
At that time,
the prosecution will produce

13:17.875 --> 13:19.000
evidence compelling enough
to sustain the case.

13:19.083 --> 13:21.375
Or I will grant Mr. Axelrod
his dismissal.

13:24.125 --> 13:27.208
♪ suspenseful music  ♪

13:27.291 --> 13:31.375
♪♪♪

13:31.458 --> 13:36.333
♪♪♪

13:36.417 --> 13:42.208
♪♪♪

13:43.291 --> 13:44.959
Hello?

13:45.041 --> 13:46.750
Our project has been
fast-tracked.

13:46.834 --> 13:49.041
It needs to be accomplished
within the week.

13:49.125 --> 13:54.000
Well, the risks in execution
are significantly greater.

13:57.000 --> 13:58.625
I'm going to need
to double my price.

13:58.709 --> 14:01.709
♪ suspenseful music  ♪

14:01.792 --> 14:03.417
So be it.

14:03.500 --> 14:07.041
♪♪♪

14:07.125 --> 14:10.625
♪♪♪

14:12.333 --> 14:14.208
You rattled?

14:14.291 --> 14:16.041
Do I look rattled?

14:16.125 --> 14:17.208
If you weren't
a little rattled,

14:17.291 --> 14:18.417
you'd have come
right to my office

14:18.500 --> 14:21.291
when you saw the top floor
annexed like that.

14:21.375 --> 14:23.417
But you played it cool.

14:23.500 --> 14:24.417
You're right.

14:24.500 --> 14:26.917
I wouldn't use the word
"rattled," but...

14:27.000 --> 14:28.500
The situation upstairs
indicates increasing odds

14:28.583 --> 14:29.917
of a worst-case scenario.

14:30.000 --> 14:33.583
And you're sitting here
trying to figure out what?

14:33.667 --> 14:34.792
It's on me to be ready

14:34.875 --> 14:36.125
to address any
subsequent instability.

14:38.542 --> 14:40.625
You're wondering
if Axe Capital can survive

14:40.709 --> 14:42.458
Axe himself
going to jail.

14:42.542 --> 14:44.208
Yes.

14:45.875 --> 14:47.500
Not as we know it.

14:47.583 --> 14:49.000
It'll be about mutation.

14:49.083 --> 14:51.208
The capital will still
need to be managed.

14:51.291 --> 14:54.250
The people here are capable
and the right ones to do it.

14:54.333 --> 14:55.917
But can it thrive, grow,

14:56.000 --> 15:00.625
and continue to really live
if Axe goes to jail?

15:00.709 --> 15:02.458
That'll come down
to one thing.

15:02.542 --> 15:05.667
You know what that is.

15:07.417 --> 15:09.291
You.

15:09.375 --> 15:10.875
But that's
not news to you.

15:10.959 --> 15:13.667
Because part of you
wants that challenge,

15:13.750 --> 15:14.959
part of you is
terrified of it,

15:15.041 --> 15:17.291
and part of you
hates yourself

15:17.375 --> 15:20.834
for hoping he does go away,
so you get a chance to see.

15:20.917 --> 15:22.709
Yes.

15:22.792 --> 15:24.208
Even now I measure myself
against him,

15:24.291 --> 15:25.458
as though he were gone.

15:25.542 --> 15:27.000
And the thought
of coming up short--

15:27.083 --> 15:29.166
Measurable successes
are seductive.

15:29.250 --> 15:31.166
Especially when
we're young.

15:32.625 --> 15:36.834
But when it comes to dealing
with other human beings,

15:36.917 --> 15:38.709
we have to steer
from instinct.

15:38.792 --> 15:39.959
I don't trust instinct.

15:40.041 --> 15:41.417
That's because
you're defining it

15:41.500 --> 15:43.375
in some woo woo
spiritual way.

15:43.458 --> 15:45.041
Don't.

15:45.125 --> 15:48.959
Instead, think of your gut
as the deepest part of you,

15:49.041 --> 15:51.125
the part that can do
internal calculations

15:51.208 --> 15:52.333
on the highest plane.

15:52.417 --> 15:54.834
Axe, at his best,
does this.

15:54.917 --> 15:58.834
You want to be on his level,
in the purest way,

15:58.917 --> 16:02.875
the most profound,
then you must, too.

16:02.959 --> 16:04.291
Identify it.

16:04.375 --> 16:07.250
Separate it
from your fears, your hopes,

16:07.333 --> 16:08.792
the other voices
in your head.

16:08.875 --> 16:12.667
Because if you don't cultivate
instinct, and listen to it--

16:12.750 --> 16:14.333
you're fucking doomed.

16:14.417 --> 16:15.500
♪ dramatic music  ♪

16:15.583 --> 16:19.208
♪♪♪

16:19.291 --> 16:21.959
♪♪♪

16:22.041 --> 16:24.333
You know what?

16:24.417 --> 16:26.375
Now I am rattled.

16:26.458 --> 16:29.417
♪♪♪

16:31.125 --> 16:35.000
Bobby, they don't
have the slide.

16:35.083 --> 16:36.875
Connerty's slow playing us.
He'll roll it out at trial.

16:36.959 --> 16:39.875
Nope. If he were,
this was the moment

16:39.959 --> 16:41.375
he would have produced it.

16:41.458 --> 16:43.917
So now, we run out the clock
and game over.

16:44.000 --> 16:45.792
It's pretty to think so.

16:45.875 --> 16:47.542
When did you
become a dyspeptic?

16:47.625 --> 16:50.333
When I started facing
jail time.

16:50.417 --> 16:52.417
When did you become
a fucking Pollyannic?

16:52.500 --> 16:54.625
You're convinced this evidence
is out there, fine.

16:54.709 --> 16:56.125
Then tell me
what you want me to do,

16:56.208 --> 16:58.083
because you're leaving me
no options.

16:58.166 --> 16:58.959
You're not interested
in taking a plea,

16:59.041 --> 17:01.208
you won't leave
the country--

17:01.291 --> 17:01.917
What's the physical
security like

17:02.000 --> 17:04.500
at the FBI
evidence lock

17:04.583 --> 17:06.875
-Come on.
-State of the art.

17:06.959 --> 17:07.834
We'll look into it.

17:07.917 --> 17:09.583
Get back to me
when you know more.

17:09.667 --> 17:12.583
♪ dramatic music  ♪

17:12.667 --> 17:17.917
♪♪♪

17:22.291 --> 17:23.208
We're almost home.

17:24.417 --> 17:28.583
Don't let your paranoia make you
take unnecessary risks.

17:28.667 --> 17:32.583
Not unnecessary if they
keep me out of jail.

17:44.834 --> 17:46.542
Come with me.

18:01.959 --> 18:05.083
I'm sorry, man.
The deal is off.

18:05.166 --> 18:07.625
Mr. Aduba--Roland--

18:07.709 --> 18:09.166
I won't accept that;
I can't.

18:09.250 --> 18:11.667
Axelrod's residence is
wrapped in barbed wire.

18:11.750 --> 18:12.709
There's simply no way

18:12.792 --> 18:14.875
to penetrate it
in a matter of days.

18:16.166 --> 18:18.875
The whole fifty.
A full refund.

18:18.959 --> 18:19.667
You know, I usually
don't do such a thing.

18:19.750 --> 18:22.250
And your family?

18:22.333 --> 18:24.375
Without me, they may never
set foot on these shores.

18:26.417 --> 18:29.417
If I'm in jail again,
then I'll be useless to them.

18:29.500 --> 18:31.000
I can shield you
from that.

18:31.083 --> 18:32.875
I cannot
perform miracles.

18:32.959 --> 18:33.667
Neither can you.

18:33.750 --> 18:37.000
♪ dramatic music  ♪

18:37.083 --> 18:39.333
♪♪♪

18:39.417 --> 18:41.083
Perhaps there's an employee
at Axe Capital

18:41.166 --> 18:43.667
you can persuade
to put it there.

18:44.208 --> 18:45.291
Such as your wife.

18:46.875 --> 18:51.458
Good luck, mukuyu.

18:51.542 --> 18:56.375
♪♪♪

18:56.458 --> 19:01.375
♪♪♪

19:01.458 --> 19:06.291
♪♪♪

19:09.041 --> 19:10.917
I didn't know
you were a runner.

19:11.000 --> 19:13.917
Just about at
my lactate threshold.

19:14.000 --> 19:15.083
Really clears the mind,

19:15.166 --> 19:18.166
optimizes my performance
at the office.

19:18.250 --> 19:20.375
Yes. Head of Compliance,
is it?

19:20.458 --> 19:23.583
That must be quite a job,
keeping those hooligans in line.

19:23.667 --> 19:26.041
I'm tough with them,
and they respect me for it.

19:26.125 --> 19:28.083
And I got to say,
it's nice

19:28.166 --> 19:30.834
working for a winner
for a change.

19:30.917 --> 19:32.125
Really.

19:33.291 --> 19:36.166
Wasn't that long ago we were
working alongside each other

19:36.250 --> 19:39.750
to nail Bobby Axelrod,
and now he's a winner?

19:39.834 --> 19:41.041
You never did nail him.

19:41.125 --> 19:42.083
Ah. Guess you
got me there.

19:42.166 --> 19:44.917
So, what can I do
for you, Chuck?

19:45.000 --> 19:47.959
It's a simple assignment,
easily accomplished.

19:49.250 --> 19:52.250
Use your access to help
close out this case

19:52.333 --> 19:54.083
against your momentary boss,

19:54.166 --> 19:57.083
then rejoin
the righteous.

19:57.166 --> 20:01.500
You want me to be
a cuckoo bird,

20:01.583 --> 20:03.208
sneaking my eggs
into another mother's nest.

20:03.291 --> 20:08.917
Yes, when the egg
cracks open: destruction.

20:09.000 --> 20:11.834
Beautiful and total.

20:11.917 --> 20:14.500
You would be
well-rewarded.

20:14.583 --> 20:17.250
Rewarded. How?

20:17.333 --> 20:19.583
Well, when Axe Capital
is inevitably found guilty

20:19.667 --> 20:23.166
of securities violations,
you have my assurance--my word--

20:23.250 --> 20:26.583
that you, as Head of Compliance,
would be protected.

20:26.667 --> 20:28.792
Look, see, the problem is:

20:28.875 --> 20:31.417
I'm not
some cuckoo bird, Chuck.

20:31.500 --> 20:32.625
I'm a golden eagle.

20:34.250 --> 20:37.083
So why would I do
anything for you?

20:37.166 --> 20:39.583
It's unfortunate
I have to say it.

20:39.667 --> 20:41.458
You know what
I have on you.

20:41.542 --> 20:45.458
You mean accusations
of a decades-old impropriety--

20:45.542 --> 20:46.250
Date rape.

20:46.333 --> 20:47.917
We're not
in Hollywood, Chuck.

20:48.000 --> 20:50.291
Nothing's gonna happen.

20:50.375 --> 20:53.583
Say it loud enough, they might
even make me president.

20:53.667 --> 20:57.166
♪ mid-tempo music  ♪

20:57.250 --> 21:00.667
♪♪♪

21:00.750 --> 21:05.375
♪♪♪

21:07.500 --> 21:09.834
Probably not your best move
right now.

21:09.917 --> 21:11.583
I need you to hear
what you wouldn't let me say

21:11.667 --> 21:13.750
-in the courtroom.
-I heard what you said.

21:13.834 --> 21:17.083
But you hear me: Men like
Axelrod do what they need to do.

21:17.166 --> 21:19.458
You counter not in here,
in the courtroom. With evidence.

21:21.333 --> 21:23.000
-In a week.

21:23.083 --> 21:24.709
Goodbye, Mr. Connerty.

21:28.959 --> 21:32.083
No!

21:32.166 --> 21:34.875
Why the hell would you risk
coming to my chambers

21:34.959 --> 21:36.041
just to turn heel
and walk out?

21:36.125 --> 21:38.875
What weak cheese is that?

21:38.959 --> 21:40.333
You said "goodbye."

21:40.417 --> 21:43.041
I'm a judge.
I give orders all day.

21:43.125 --> 21:44.291
You're a litigator.

21:44.375 --> 21:47.583
You find a way to disobey them
without getting nailed for it.

21:47.667 --> 21:50.834
Then I'm not leaving
until you give me an answer.

21:54.291 --> 21:57.667
That sensation you're feeling,
it's known as the Dip.

21:57.750 --> 21:58.834
Seth Godin coined it.

21:58.917 --> 22:00.959
Feels like the moment
before defeat.

22:01.041 --> 22:03.917
It's actually the moment
before success.

22:04.000 --> 22:06.083
Feels more
like Death Valley.

22:06.166 --> 22:08.208
You care so fucking much.
I love that.

22:08.291 --> 22:09.709
I love that.
You're meant for this shit.

22:09.792 --> 22:11.750
Dig in, man.

22:11.834 --> 22:13.250
The world has lost
countless artists and artisans

22:13.333 --> 22:16.333
and engineers
and even politicians who quit

22:16.417 --> 22:18.583
because they cared too much
to come up short

22:18.667 --> 22:21.417
and yet also too much
to keep going.

22:21.500 --> 22:23.333
You push through that Dip
right now,

22:23.417 --> 22:25.625
maybe you put Axelrod
where he needs to be.

22:31.000 --> 22:32.917
Why are you
out of breath?

22:33.000 --> 22:35.583
Bike ride.
I have a recumbent.

22:35.667 --> 22:36.333
Great for the hills
out here.

22:36.417 --> 22:39.417
Of course.
More aerodynamic.

22:39.500 --> 22:40.583
Where are you?

22:40.667 --> 22:42.250
Meditation room.

22:42.333 --> 22:44.750
Oh. I'll go
to mine, too!

22:46.792 --> 22:48.250
Why you hiding out
in there?

22:48.333 --> 22:50.709
I'm not hiding.
My office has been commandeered.

22:50.792 --> 22:52.542
I'm working through issues
with my algorithm

22:52.625 --> 22:54.500
and it's the only place
that's quiet.

22:54.583 --> 22:55.917
You ran
another back

22:56.000 --> 22:58.125
My programmers didn't
correct for slippage.

22:58.208 --> 22:59.208
They're software,
not finance.

22:59.291 --> 23:01.625
I have a vision for it
that I haven't yet been able

23:01.709 --> 23:03.083
to realize in my design.

23:03.166 --> 23:04.750
A phrase uttered
by the architect

23:04.834 --> 23:06.625
of every great invention.

23:06.709 --> 23:08.667
I can keep tweaking it
and improve it incrementally,

23:08.750 --> 23:09.667
or--

23:09.750 --> 23:11.959
Or start over.

23:13.500 --> 23:14.792
Crap. Yes.

23:14.875 --> 23:16.083
I'd have to gut it.

23:16.166 --> 23:18.583
Feel like I just
kicked over your Lego city.

23:19.542 --> 23:22.458
What you said is true.
Just frustrating.

23:22.542 --> 23:26.166
Breaking trail
is a lonely calling.

23:26.250 --> 23:27.000
Hang in.

23:27.083 --> 23:30.125
♪ dramatic music  ♪

23:30.208 --> 23:32.917
♪♪♪

23:33.000 --> 23:34.917
♪♪♪

23:35.000 --> 23:37.083
Fuck.

23:37.166 --> 23:38.375
Uh-oh.

23:41.000 --> 23:42.542
Send in Orrin Bach.

23:42.625 --> 23:43.709
--They're gonna like
this. You're doing a great job.

23:43.792 --> 23:45.417
-I promise.
-Sorry.

23:46.709 --> 23:50.291
I know I'm not allowed
in the clubhouse, but Axe?

23:50.375 --> 23:52.917
The baton is
in my hand.

23:53.000 --> 23:55.834
Sign this standard
retainer letter.

23:58.583 --> 23:59.792
You know what my favorite
Olympic event is?

24:02.000 --> 24:04.875
It's the four
by 100 meter relay.

24:04.959 --> 24:06.667
Because it's
about teamwork.

24:06.750 --> 24:08.458
It's about the pass.

24:08.542 --> 24:11.333
Right now,
I've got the baton.

24:11.417 --> 24:13.166
But I'm passing it
to you, Axe.

24:13.250 --> 24:14.834
You're the anchor.

24:14.917 --> 24:16.083
You're gonna
bring it home.

24:16.166 --> 24:18.000
You are gonna win.

24:18.083 --> 24:19.500
What am I gonna win?

24:19.583 --> 24:20.625
Your case.

24:20.709 --> 24:21.750
Because of the baton?

24:21.834 --> 24:23.041
Yes.

24:23.125 --> 24:24.250
Which in this case
is not an actual baton,

24:24.333 --> 24:28.542
but is Dr. Wendy Rhoades.

24:29.917 --> 24:32.417
I've been doing a little
sleuthing about the IPO;

24:32.500 --> 24:33.417
you know,
winners and losers.

24:33.500 --> 24:36.583
And I discover
that one particular fund

24:36.667 --> 24:38.417
made a killing that day
shorting the stock.

24:38.500 --> 24:40.500
So I look to see
whose account it is,

24:40.583 --> 24:43.458
and I notice
there's an irregularity.

24:43.542 --> 24:45.792
So I keep digging,

24:45.875 --> 24:48.792
and lo and behold--
it's Wendy's.

24:48.875 --> 24:52.500
The name on the account had been
flipped with someone else's.

24:52.583 --> 24:54.458
Now this is the first time
she has ever even made a trade,

24:54.542 --> 24:57.875
herself, in her whole history
at Axe Cap.

24:57.959 --> 25:00.333
So I get a buddy of mine who
works for the NSA to find out

25:00.417 --> 25:02.083
where she was
when she called in

25:02.166 --> 25:03.583
-the order for the short.
-Wait.

25:03.667 --> 25:05.125
You had the NSA
look into Wendy?

25:05.208 --> 25:06.917
Completely off-book.

25:07.000 --> 25:08.333
But guess
where it pinged?

25:08.417 --> 25:11.917
Southern District
of New York.

25:12.000 --> 25:13.542
Chuck's office.

25:13.625 --> 25:18.000
We got some real
Whitewater shit here.

25:18.083 --> 25:20.542
Needless to say: with this
in Bryan Connerty's hands,

25:20.625 --> 25:23.375
the spotlight
moves off of you

25:23.458 --> 25:26.959
and shines all over
Mr. and Mrs. Rhoades.

25:27.041 --> 25:28.583
Chaos grenade.

25:32.041 --> 25:34.542
If this were
the four by 100 meter relay,

25:34.625 --> 25:37.500
you would be disqualified for
sniffing glue on the team bus.

25:37.583 --> 25:39.041
This is
the worst fucking idea

25:39.125 --> 25:41.250
anyone's brought me
in over a year.

25:41.333 --> 25:42.375
Um--

25:42.458 --> 25:44.291
Eh, you know, I am
gonna try and forget

25:44.375 --> 25:45.917
we just had
this little moment.

25:46.000 --> 25:48.959
Also, the two thousand that
I spent retaining Bach for you.

25:53.208 --> 25:54.792
He's not wrong.

25:54.875 --> 25:57.458
Exposing Wendy's short
could be good for us;

25:57.542 --> 25:58.625
I've said it before.

25:58.709 --> 26:01.625
Yeah, and I've said:
she is off limits.

26:02.542 --> 26:02.875
You still here?

26:04.875 --> 26:06.875
Problem is:
I already told Connerty.

26:08.542 --> 26:10.959
I went full Le Carré.

26:11.041 --> 26:13.959
♪ suspenseful music  ♪

26:14.041 --> 26:18.625
♪♪♪

26:18.709 --> 26:22.250
♪ dramatic music  ♪

26:22.333 --> 26:27.166
♪♪♪

26:28.750 --> 26:30.667
The only reason
you're not flying

26:30.750 --> 26:33.458
is because
these windows don't open.

26:33.542 --> 26:35.667
And we can't fire you right now
because it wouldn't look good.

26:35.750 --> 26:38.333
But get the fuck
out of our sight.

26:38.417 --> 26:41.083
And stay there.

26:41.166 --> 26:43.583
♪ dramatic music  ♪

26:43.667 --> 26:46.125
♪♪♪

26:46.208 --> 26:48.792
♪♪♪

26:48.875 --> 26:50.959
I have to tell her.

26:52.125 --> 26:54.083
Fuck.

26:55.250 --> 26:57.000
Godspeed.

26:57.083 --> 26:58.750
♪ slow distorted music  ♪

26:58.834 --> 27:03.000
♪♪♪

27:03.083 --> 27:07.625
♪♪♪

27:07.709 --> 27:11.166
♪♪♪

27:11.250 --> 27:16.500
♪♪♪

27:16.583 --> 27:20.041
♪♪♪

27:20.125 --> 27:25.333
♪♪♪

27:25.417 --> 27:29.834
♪♪♪

27:29.917 --> 27:31.125
Come in.

27:38.625 --> 27:39.834
Are you okay?

27:39.917 --> 27:41.041
♪ dramatic music  ♪

27:41.125 --> 27:44.625
♪♪♪

27:44.709 --> 27:46.250
Bobby. Out with it.

27:49.041 --> 27:50.083
The Feds have
your Ice Juice short.

27:50.166 --> 27:55.458
♪♪♪

27:55.542 --> 27:59.208
It was Spyros.
To Connerty.

27:59.291 --> 28:01.250
He thought he was helping me.
I just found out.

28:02.333 --> 28:04.291
Are you sure
it wasn't you?

28:05.417 --> 28:08.250
Not how it happened.
I promise.

28:08.333 --> 28:12.500
♪♪♪

28:12.583 --> 28:16.166
♪♪♪

28:18.333 --> 28:19.917
So, Spyros.

28:20.000 --> 28:21.417
He gave
him everything:

28:21.500 --> 28:24.291
size of the position,
your trading history.

28:24.375 --> 28:26.083
Even when and where
you called in the order.

28:26.166 --> 28:28.083
I could...

28:28.166 --> 28:31.917
Chuck has said if these events
get interpreted in this way--

28:32.000 --> 28:33.333
painting me
as a co-conspirator--

28:33.417 --> 28:34.458
I  could end up...

28:34.542 --> 28:36.000
Yes. Jail.

28:36.083 --> 28:36.792
But I will not
let that happen.

28:36.875 --> 28:38.792
I'll get you whatever
you need.

28:38.875 --> 28:40.834
The best lawyers;
I'll pay for everything.

28:40.917 --> 28:42.542
You have the best lawyers.
Look where you're at.

28:42.625 --> 28:45.250
I thought
I had this locked down.

28:45.333 --> 28:46.542
Well, you didn't.

28:46.625 --> 28:50.625
♪♪♪

28:50.709 --> 28:53.333
I know you did what you did
with the same intention:

28:53.417 --> 28:55.625
to protect
those you love.

28:56.875 --> 29:00.375
And I, too, failed.

29:00.458 --> 29:03.792
♪♪♪

29:03.875 --> 29:08.208
What words do you need me to say
to make you feel safe?

29:08.709 --> 29:10.709
Are there any?

29:10.792 --> 29:11.875
Really?

29:13.625 --> 29:15.375
No. Not really.

29:17.208 --> 29:18.709
Right.

29:20.750 --> 29:21.250
I need to go.

29:21.333 --> 29:27.083
♪♪♪

29:27.166 --> 29:31.208
How do you communicate
with people?

29:31.291 --> 29:31.959
In these kinds
of situations?

29:32.041 --> 29:33.375
Oh. Here.
Take my burner.

29:33.458 --> 29:35.375
Don't you need it?

29:35.458 --> 29:37.000
No. I got plenty.

29:37.083 --> 29:39.000
Call me anytime.

29:39.083 --> 29:41.583
♪♪♪

29:41.667 --> 29:44.291
♪♪♪

29:44.375 --> 29:46.208
It's me.

29:46.291 --> 29:47.875
I need to see you.

29:50.125 --> 29:52.750
Remember back when I
asked you for those SEC files?

29:52.834 --> 29:54.375
The transactions
of all the people

29:54.458 --> 29:55.834
who bought and sold stock
in the Ice Juice IPO?

29:55.917 --> 29:58.250
You know how you never
got them for me?

30:02.625 --> 30:04.583
I got 'em anyway.

30:04.667 --> 30:05.625
Tell me again
how we have to leave Chuck

30:05.709 --> 30:08.208
out of this investigation.

30:08.291 --> 30:10.041
♪ suspenseful music  ♪

30:10.125 --> 30:13.959
♪♪♪

30:16.542 --> 30:18.959
Forgive me, Lord.

30:20.458 --> 30:22.709
You're right.

30:22.792 --> 30:23.333
It's time.

30:23.417 --> 30:28.166
♪♪♪

30:28.250 --> 30:31.959
♪♪♪

30:32.041 --> 30:35.792
♪♪♪

30:35.875 --> 30:39.583
♪♪♪

30:39.667 --> 30:43.458
♪♪♪

30:44.834 --> 30:47.250
♪ ominous music  ♪

30:47.333 --> 30:50.875
♪♪♪

30:50.959 --> 30:54.250
♪♪♪

30:54.333 --> 30:57.917
♪♪♪

30:58.000 --> 31:01.291
♪♪♪

31:01.375 --> 31:05.375
♪♪♪

31:05.458 --> 31:07.166
It wasn't Axe;
Axe is fighting for me.

31:09.625 --> 31:11.625
Ari Spyros told him.

31:14.166 --> 31:16.333
He thought he was
protecting Axe.

31:16.417 --> 31:19.083
Yeah. And he knew
he was fucking me.

31:19.166 --> 31:21.792
How are we gonna
make this okay?

31:21.875 --> 31:23.959
♪♪♪

31:24.041 --> 31:26.041
Chuck! I need you
to tell me something.

31:26.125 --> 31:30.875
There is one avenue
that may still be open to us.

31:32.000 --> 31:33.083
Connerty?

31:34.166 --> 31:36.125
I need to make him
want to get Axelrod

31:36.208 --> 31:37.834
more than he wants
to get me.

31:37.917 --> 31:42.125
♪♪♪

31:42.208 --> 31:46.291
♪♪♪

31:46.375 --> 31:50.834
♪♪♪

31:52.542 --> 31:54.792
What if I took a plea?

31:54.875 --> 31:58.291
I understand you have
an attachment to Wendy,

31:58.375 --> 32:02.291
but this isn't just a question
of you sacrificing yourself.

32:03.333 --> 32:05.125
In every battle
there are casualties.

32:05.208 --> 32:07.500
You're talking about
surrendering your kingdom

32:07.583 --> 32:09.375
to save a single
loyal soldier.

32:09.458 --> 32:10.917
She saved me.

32:11.000 --> 32:12.750
And she's not just
a loyal soldier,

32:12.834 --> 32:16.208
she's the company's
fucking spirit animal.

32:16.291 --> 32:19.166
My people come unglued,
she puts them back together,

32:19.250 --> 32:21.041
and better than
they were before.

32:21.125 --> 32:23.041
Your own personal
Oscar Goldman.

32:23.125 --> 32:24.291
If you will.

32:24.834 --> 32:27.542
You owe her, too.

32:27.625 --> 32:29.917
That spread of yours
out in Sagaponack?

32:31.417 --> 32:32.959
You wouldn't have that
without me,

32:33.041 --> 32:36.959
and I wouldn't have
Axe Cap without her.

32:38.500 --> 32:39.458
You'd have to
make a statement

32:39.542 --> 32:42.917
that precludes any notion
that you were baited.

32:43.000 --> 32:46.750
Otherwise Connerty could still
pursue them for conspiracy.

32:46.834 --> 32:49.083
You'd be absolving
Chuck Rhoades of any blame.

32:51.583 --> 32:53.208
You'll get
seven years. Minimum.

32:53.291 --> 32:57.208
And you'll do over 80 percent
of it because it's Federal.

32:57.291 --> 32:57.917
Lara will be a pariah.

32:58.000 --> 32:59.959
Your sons
will be scarred;

33:00.041 --> 33:01.792
it'll haunt them
all their lives.

33:01.875 --> 33:04.542
Maybe more
than it will yours.

33:04.625 --> 33:06.709
♪ suspenseful music  ♪

33:06.792 --> 33:08.917
♪♪♪

33:09.000 --> 33:11.208
I'll let you know
what I decide.

33:17.041 --> 33:20.417
-Jesus Christ.
-When you're hungry in an hour,

33:20.500 --> 33:22.041
go get yourself
some real sashimi.

33:22.125 --> 33:23.625
Oh, god.
Is that pineapple?

33:23.709 --> 33:25.709
You got something to say to me,
do it through proper channels.

33:25.792 --> 33:28.417
Don't hijack my lunch.

33:28.500 --> 33:31.834
Or open your mouth and make
things even worse for yourself.

33:31.917 --> 33:33.917
There's nothing
you can offer me anymore

33:34.000 --> 33:34.875
to keep yourself
out of this.

33:34.959 --> 33:37.458
There's a chance
your wife can.

33:37.542 --> 33:40.583
If she says exactly what I need
her to, in court, under oath.

33:40.667 --> 33:41.709
You won't even
do me the courtesy

33:41.792 --> 33:42.750
of listening for a minute

33:42.834 --> 33:46.709
-to what I have--
-Oh, I'll do you a courtesy:

33:46.792 --> 33:48.500
I'm gonna come by
your house tonight,

33:48.583 --> 33:49.458
and the three of us
will talk.

33:49.542 --> 33:51.458
On the record.

33:51.542 --> 33:53.750
So whatever you want to say,
save it for there.

33:53.834 --> 33:55.375
And get Wendy ready, too.

33:59.208 --> 34:02.250
If you'd rather do it
in an interview room at Eastern,

34:02.333 --> 34:05.709
that's okay by me--
but you better bring a lawyer.

34:05.792 --> 34:08.208
And I bet it isn't
gonna be Ira Schirmer.

34:20.875 --> 34:22.083
Redecorating?

34:23.041 --> 34:24.458
Bedroom, yeah.

34:24.542 --> 34:26.875
You here to help me
pick out the duvet?

34:26.959 --> 34:29.208
No, I'm here
to give you a heads-up.

34:31.208 --> 34:32.959
I think I'm gonna
take a plea.

34:33.041 --> 34:33.834
You swore
you'd never do that.

34:33.917 --> 34:36.208
Well, things
have changed.

34:36.291 --> 34:38.083
Like what?

34:38.166 --> 34:39.625
Doesn't matter.

34:42.041 --> 34:43.208
So what does this mean?
You're going to jail?

34:45.208 --> 34:47.750
We're gonna need to work out
a visitation plan.

34:47.834 --> 34:48.834
Figure out what's best
for the boys.

34:48.917 --> 34:52.583
We'd probably move.

34:52.667 --> 34:53.834
Maybe California.

34:54.875 --> 34:56.291
You'd move?

34:56.375 --> 34:58.875
You just said we need to figure
out what's best for the boys,

34:58.959 --> 35:00.750
and that's
what would be best.

35:00.834 --> 35:02.792
What, them never seeing me?

35:02.875 --> 35:04.333
They barely see you now.

35:04.417 --> 35:08.166
And that hurts them, but at
least they still worship you.

35:08.250 --> 35:09.667
I'd be protecting that.

35:09.750 --> 35:11.667
You'd be ripping my heart
out of my chest.

35:11.750 --> 35:13.750
I'll do it
without hesitating.

35:13.834 --> 35:16.542
And no family court judge will
stop me with you in prison.

35:17.625 --> 35:18.959
What do you think
it'd be like for the kids,

35:19.041 --> 35:22.500
going to see their dad
on the inside?

35:22.583 --> 35:24.542
Do you really want them
seeing you cut down like that?

35:24.625 --> 35:27.417
No.

35:27.500 --> 35:29.291
I don't want
any of this.

35:29.375 --> 35:30.166
But California?

35:30.250 --> 35:32.500
Yeah, it's better
not to be surrounded

35:32.583 --> 35:34.125
by people
who know who you are.

35:34.208 --> 35:38.834
Not to mention
where you are, and why.

35:38.917 --> 35:41.000
Be too hard on them.

35:41.083 --> 35:43.542
♪ slow music  ♪

35:43.625 --> 35:45.834
♪♪♪

35:45.917 --> 35:50.458
Bobby, you and I...

35:50.542 --> 35:53.583
we ended up here,
for now,

35:53.667 --> 35:56.959
but I know I didn't make
a mistake about you when we met.

35:57.041 --> 35:58.959
About who you were.

35:59.041 --> 36:01.500
Who you are.

36:01.583 --> 36:04.000
And that guy would
never give in,

36:04.083 --> 36:07.709
because that guy would never
believe, even for one second,

36:07.792 --> 36:10.291
that he couldn't find a way
to convince not one,

36:10.375 --> 36:13.750
but all twelve jurors
to see things his way.

36:13.834 --> 36:17.250
Especially if it meant
losing not only his freedom,

36:17.333 --> 36:19.542
but his family.

36:19.625 --> 36:23.166
♪♪♪

36:23.250 --> 36:26.834
♪♪♪

36:35.500 --> 36:38.375
When we spoke this morning,
you were in California.

36:38.458 --> 36:39.625
Too much?

36:39.709 --> 36:42.417
I've been dealing with this
with my performance coach.

36:42.500 --> 36:45.083
I can be...unreserved,

36:45.166 --> 36:46.917
a quality others
have found off-putting.

36:47.000 --> 36:48.458
I don't.
Not in the least.

36:52.458 --> 36:54.083
Twizzlers, Bit O' Honeys,
Juicy Fruit.

36:54.166 --> 36:56.625
Standard coding provisions.

36:56.709 --> 36:58.583
You came to help me
with the algorithm?

36:58.667 --> 37:00.917
To keep you company.
You don't need my help.

37:02.083 --> 37:04.125
I'm grateful,
but I have to wonder

37:04.208 --> 37:06.041
if this is really
the best use of your time.

37:06.125 --> 37:06.875
Or your jet.

37:06.959 --> 37:09.083
This morning
you got me thinking

37:09.166 --> 37:11.125
about my first job
in Silicon Valley.

37:11.208 --> 37:13.000
The whole time
I worked there, we never knew

37:13.083 --> 37:15.125
if the company was gonna be
alive at the end of the day.

37:15.208 --> 37:15.959
So?

37:16.041 --> 37:17.959
We kept our heads down
and grinded.

37:18.041 --> 37:19.709
My work was exciting.

37:19.792 --> 37:22.083
But there were nights...
I'd be in my cube,

37:22.166 --> 37:23.458
the only one around.

37:23.542 --> 37:25.709
I remember feeling like
it would've been nice

37:25.792 --> 37:28.959
to have someone around
to play Dragon Quest with.

37:29.041 --> 37:31.083
♪ slow music  ♪

37:31.166 --> 37:33.166
We'll go to my place.
I'll get my coat.

37:33.250 --> 37:38.166
♪♪♪

37:38.250 --> 37:42.250
♪♪♪

37:42.333 --> 37:45.333
I know you and Dake
had some kind of deal.

37:45.417 --> 37:47.500
Kind of had it figured
from day one.

37:47.583 --> 37:51.458
I mean, how does that guy
get appointed U.S. Attorney?

37:53.291 --> 37:56.166
But things got
really interesting

37:56.250 --> 37:58.333
the day your best friend
was supposed to testify

37:58.417 --> 38:01.583
against Axelrod--and instead
came in and rolled on you.

38:03.750 --> 38:05.458
Whatever Ira
may have said--

38:05.542 --> 38:07.458
Sure, I know.

38:07.542 --> 38:11.750
He's a disgruntled investor.

38:11.834 --> 38:13.125
Hmm? That's what
your dad said.

38:13.208 --> 38:14.625
He's looking at
a perjury charge

38:14.709 --> 38:16.333
when I puncture
that bullshit affidavit--

38:16.417 --> 38:17.583
but that's later.

38:17.667 --> 38:19.500
Ira said
you baited Axelrod,

38:19.583 --> 38:24.792
which, I admit, seemed
a little farfetched.

38:26.333 --> 38:28.625
And then I learned
about the role Wendy played.

38:30.792 --> 38:34.792
And Ira's statement began
to seem pretty credible.

38:36.166 --> 38:39.375
I know it all sounds...
very bad.

38:39.458 --> 38:42.083
And I might conclude
the same thing if I was you,

38:42.166 --> 38:45.166
but you have to believe me,
I didn't have  a role.

38:45.250 --> 38:47.041
There was no conspiracy.

38:47.125 --> 38:50.417
A jury's gonna have a really
hard time buying that.

38:50.500 --> 38:52.542
It's a little premature
to be talking about juries.

38:52.625 --> 38:53.959
There doesn't have to
be a jury at all.

38:54.041 --> 38:56.083
You can turn yourself in
right now.

38:56.166 --> 38:59.417
This can go
one of two ways.

38:59.500 --> 39:01.333
You decide
to fight this,

39:01.417 --> 39:05.208
and I charge the two of you
equally as co-conspirators.

39:05.291 --> 39:07.166
Or, you both
take a plea

39:07.250 --> 39:10.750
and cooperate
against Axe.

39:10.834 --> 39:12.583
Chuck'll do time
but you won't.

39:12.667 --> 39:14.917
Whatever the medical board
decides to do with you

39:15.000 --> 39:17.417
is their business--
but at least Kevin and Eva

39:17.500 --> 39:20.583
will have someone
at home with them.

39:20.667 --> 39:22.917
♪ dramatic music  ♪

39:23.000 --> 39:25.917
What is this really
about for you?

39:26.000 --> 39:28.208
I think you used to have
a moral compass.

39:28.291 --> 39:30.709
And it served you--

39:30.792 --> 39:32.667
got you where you are,
made you great.

39:32.750 --> 39:37.583
Then it got warped,
or broken.

39:38.834 --> 39:40.875
But mine wasn't.

39:40.959 --> 39:43.291
And you saw that
and it killed you.

39:43.375 --> 39:45.792
So you found
a way to use it

39:45.875 --> 39:48.125
and my loyalty
to your advantage.

39:48.208 --> 39:50.792
Oh, by making sure you lead
the Axelrod investigation?

39:50.875 --> 39:51.959
By getting rid of me.

39:52.041 --> 39:54.208
Shipping me to Eastern
so I wouldn't be around

39:54.291 --> 39:55.792
to see you pulling
Dake's strings.

39:55.875 --> 39:58.291
I have done nothing
but guide you.

39:58.375 --> 40:01.667
Mentor you, prepare you
to take my place

40:01.750 --> 40:03.291
at that office.

40:03.375 --> 40:06.000
I gave you yet another
career-making case,

40:06.083 --> 40:07.458
and you fucked it up

40:07.542 --> 40:09.250
by focusing on me
and some phantom crime

40:09.333 --> 40:11.625
you think
my wife and I committed.

40:15.875 --> 40:19.625
Next time we talk,
there should be lawyers present.

40:19.709 --> 40:21.834
♪ dramatic music  ♪

40:21.917 --> 40:24.917
♪♪♪

40:25.000 --> 40:29.125
♪♪♪

40:29.208 --> 40:31.291
You know who this is?

40:31.375 --> 40:33.333
He works for Axelrod.

40:33.417 --> 40:36.959
♪♪♪

40:37.041 --> 40:39.375
That's okay.

40:39.458 --> 40:41.583
I'll wait until you're in
the witness box, under oath.

40:41.667 --> 40:46.166
♪♪♪

40:46.250 --> 40:50.709
♪♪♪

40:50.792 --> 40:55.000
I feel bad...for the kids.

40:55.083 --> 40:57.667
♪ suspenseful music  ♪

40:57.750 --> 41:02.375
♪♪♪

41:06.458 --> 41:08.333
We're gonna need lawyers.

41:08.417 --> 41:10.000
Separate ones.

41:11.667 --> 41:13.959
Keep even one of us
out of prison.

41:16.000 --> 41:18.041
♪ suspenseful music  ♪

41:18.125 --> 41:22.291
♪♪♪

41:22.375 --> 41:25.834
♪♪♪

41:25.917 --> 41:28.625
If I ever do have
a last supper,

41:28.709 --> 41:30.792
it's gonna be hard
to top this.

41:30.875 --> 41:34.291
Which is why I wanted you
to have the ortolan tonight,

41:34.375 --> 41:37.917
commander, as a reminder
of how alive you yet are.

41:41.291 --> 41:42.041
Wylie, how do I eat it?

41:42.125 --> 41:44.500
Whole, sir.

41:44.583 --> 41:46.750
In France, ortolan were
only ever to be eaten

41:46.834 --> 41:47.959
by royalty
or in the monasteries.

41:48.041 --> 41:51.333
And hunters would
bring them as absolute tribute

41:51.417 --> 41:52.959
for being allowed
to work the land.

41:53.041 --> 41:55.709
The birds are trapped
where grapes grow

41:55.792 --> 41:58.625
so their insides have
the flavor of the terroir,

41:58.709 --> 42:00.291
the taste,
of the land,

42:00.375 --> 42:01.458
all the way down
to the guts and the bones.

42:01.542 --> 42:04.166
Which is why
we don't carve them.

42:04.250 --> 42:05.083
It's against the law
to eat them

42:05.166 --> 42:06.792
in France now, isn't it?

42:06.875 --> 42:08.083
Illegal the world over.

42:08.166 --> 42:09.834
Because there are those
who don't recognize

42:09.917 --> 42:10.959
what truly matters.

42:11.041 --> 42:12.500
Because they're
so delicious?

42:12.583 --> 42:14.917
Because, in a crueler time,
they were blinded.

42:15.000 --> 42:15.834
Their eyes would
be gouged out

42:15.917 --> 42:18.208
so they would think
it was nighttime,

42:18.291 --> 42:19.125
which
makes them ravenous.

42:19.208 --> 42:20.917
So they would
gorge themselves

42:21.000 --> 42:23.750
until they were three times
their natural size.

42:23.834 --> 42:25.208
That we don't do anymore.

42:25.291 --> 42:27.333
But it's still
death by Armagnac,

42:27.417 --> 42:28.750
they're drowned in it.

42:30.041 --> 42:32.500
Very much
how I'd like to go.

42:32.583 --> 42:34.875
♪ slow music  ♪

42:34.959 --> 42:38.291
♪♪♪

42:38.375 --> 42:41.041
♪♪♪

42:41.125 --> 42:45.458
♪♪♪

42:55.917 --> 42:58.166
Mmm.

42:59.583 --> 43:01.792
Mmm.

43:01.875 --> 43:03.291
Mmm.

43:03.375 --> 43:04.750
Mmm.

43:04.834 --> 43:05.125
Mmm.

43:05.208 --> 43:08.834
♪♪♪

43:08.917 --> 43:11.959
♪♪♪

43:13.583 --> 43:18.333
♪♪♪

43:18.417 --> 43:20.500
I don't know about you,

43:20.583 --> 43:23.583
but I just had
a religious experience.

43:25.125 --> 43:28.792
At the climax I felt the crack
of its little rib cage,

43:28.875 --> 43:33.792
then the hot juices
rushing out down my gullet.

43:35.583 --> 43:36.083
Sublime.

43:36.166 --> 43:38.000
Yes.

43:39.041 --> 43:40.166
It was.

43:41.125 --> 43:42.500
Got any more?

43:42.583 --> 43:44.500
I'm still
a little peckish.

43:44.583 --> 43:46.750
You know what
they say about ortolan--

43:46.834 --> 43:49.166
one is bliss,
two is gluttony.

43:49.250 --> 43:50.709
How about three?

43:50.792 --> 43:51.917
Let's find out.

44:01.917 --> 44:06.625
♪♪♪

44:06.709 --> 44:11.375
♪♪♪

44:11.458 --> 44:14.041
How you doing?

44:14.125 --> 44:16.542
A bit like one of those
little birds we just ate

44:16.625 --> 44:18.542
right before
they turn out the lights.

44:18.625 --> 44:22.875
♪♪♪

44:22.959 --> 44:27.291
♪♪♪

44:27.375 --> 44:29.542
You know what
this reminds me of?

44:29.625 --> 44:31.583
The night we cracked
ten billion.

44:31.667 --> 44:35.834
You and me,
night fishing off City Island.

44:35.917 --> 44:37.583
What a beautiful
fucking night.

44:37.667 --> 44:41.417
Stars out,
stripers hitting.

44:41.500 --> 44:44.041
One tub full of fish,
the other tub full of bourbon.

44:44.125 --> 44:45.083
Most newly minted
deca-billionaires

44:45.166 --> 44:46.875
would have checked out
with a few Spiegler girls

44:46.959 --> 44:50.542
and enough mushrooms for
a three day binge in Chamonix.

44:50.625 --> 44:52.250
How often do you get
to come home at dawn

44:52.333 --> 44:54.542
with six striped bass
in your trunk?

44:54.625 --> 44:56.583
♪♪♪

44:56.667 --> 45:00.417
Jesus, what
the fuck happened.

45:00.500 --> 45:03.542
You fought the law.

45:03.625 --> 45:05.083
The law won.

45:06.959 --> 45:09.583
I'm going out
to face them alone.

45:09.667 --> 45:11.583
You slip out the back.

45:11.667 --> 45:13.041
I'll be fine.

45:14.375 --> 45:16.125
Yeah, you will.

45:16.208 --> 45:18.125
So will you.

45:18.709 --> 45:20.917
I'm gonna miss you.

45:23.208 --> 45:24.875
Thanks for the friendship.

45:25.959 --> 45:28.208
[David Ramirez's
"I'm Not Going Anywhere"]

45:28.291 --> 45:32.875
♪♪♪

45:32.959 --> 45:37.250
♪♪♪

45:37.333 --> 45:40.625
♪♪♪

45:42.125 --> 45:45.125
♪ I'm not going anywhere  ♪

45:45.208 --> 45:47.542
♪♪♪

45:47.625 --> 45:53.333
♪ No, I'm not going anywhere  ♪

45:53.417 --> 45:55.834
♪♪♪

45:55.917 --> 45:58.750
♪ You can bury me
in the ground  ♪

46:00.083 --> 46:02.166
♪ Or spread my ash  ♪

46:02.250 --> 46:04.667
♪ I don't care  ♪

46:04.750 --> 46:08.834
♪ I'm not going anywhere  ♪

46:08.917 --> 46:12.834
♪♪♪

46:12.917 --> 46:14.667
Oh, did I wake you?

46:14.750 --> 46:16.458
No.

46:16.542 --> 46:18.583
Where'd you get that?

46:18.667 --> 46:22.250
Oh, I came down looking for
the rest of Eva's birthday cake.

46:22.333 --> 46:23.250
You told me to toss it.

46:23.333 --> 46:28.458
So I walked to the corner deli
and I got this.

46:30.583 --> 46:33.250
